rComments: Most of the lectures were given by guest lecturers, and often the slides were not posted online so going to class is an absolute must in this course, but they're very fun and enjoyable if you're interested in forensic science. I would literally look forward to the lectures. The assignments were hard to ace, but she's generally a great prof
teacherRatingTags: ['Amazing lectures', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: Professor Luk is great. She facilitates the lectures, but all lectures are done by guests. The tests were surprisingly easy. The lectures are usually very interesting which makes coming to class a pleasure.

Honestly one of the best professors I've ever had. The course was a little heavy but Prof. Luk made herself available to us for help. She also made emotional connections with most of the students. Highly recommend taking any of her classes.

Professor Luk provided an indepth overview of Analytical Toxicology. This is being turned into a full course (FSC40?), expect it to be harder when it is. Very interesting content, but you need passion to do well
The best looking professor on campus on UTM.

I have a lot of respect for her. She goes out of her way to help students. Her lectures were great! She is passionate about her work, extremely caring and kind hearted, and really wants her students to do well. In my entire academic career, I have never met a prof like her. She is truly a gem!
